Spin up AWS environment at:
https://catalog.demo.redhat.com/catalog?item=babylon-catalog-prod/sandboxes-gpte.sandbox-open.prod&utm_source=webapp&utm_medium=share-link

Record login credentials.
Open Web Console Access page (unique for each environment)
Apply Login credentials (provided after environment has been created)
Click "View all services" from widget
Click "EC2" under 'Compute'
Click 'Launch Instance'
Name your instance, ie "Bastion"
Click 'Red Hat' under Quick Start
From AMI drop down, select RHEL 9
Click Confirm Changes if prompted
Generate New Key Pair if desired or use a currently available one
Create a new default VPC if required, or select a VPC (may need to refresh after you create default VPC for it to show in drop down)
Create a new subnet or select one from the list
Select DHCP Option
Configure storage to be at least 500GB (recommended)
Configure any Advanced Details as needed
Click 'Launch Instance'
Click 'connect to instance'  Connect how you desire, either via ssh or session manager (recommend ssh)
Create a directory to work in, ie 'openshift'

Downloading binaries:
Login to console.redhat.com
Click OpenShift
On left hand side click 'Downloads'
Scroll down to the bottom and copy your pull secret and store on your bastion
Note* May have to install VIM editor (sudo yum innstall vim and/or install wget)
Right click on 'Download' link next to 'Openshift client (oc) mirro plugin, select 'copy link address'
On bastion CLI, type 'wget https://mirror.openshift.com/pub/openshift-v4/x86_64/clients/ocp/latest/oc-mirror.rhel9.tar.gz'
Right click on 'Download' link next to mirror registry for OpenShift, select 'copy link address'
On bastion CLI, type 'wget https://mirror.openshift.com/pub/cgw/mirror-registry/latest/mirror-registry-amd64.tar.gz'
Right click on 'Download' link next to OpenShift installer
on Bastion CLI, type 'wget https://mirror.openshift.com/pub/openshift-v4/x86_64/clients/ocp/stable/openshift-install-linux.tar.gz'

Documentation for oc-mirror:  https://docs.redhat.com/en/documentation/openshift_container_platform/4.12/html/disconnected_installation_mirroring/installing-mirroring-disconnected
Install OC mirror, tar xvzf oc-mirror.rhel9.tar.gz
chmod +x oc-mirror
sudo mv oc-mirror /usr/local/bin/.
Verify oc-mirror installation:  oc-mirror help  (note, need '-' between oc and mirror even though documentation says to use 'oc mirror' as the command)
convert pull secret to a json file:
cat ./pull-secret | jq . > config.json
mv config.json ~/.docker/config.json
tar xvzf mirror-registry-amd64.tar.gz
sudo yum install podman
Run command:  './mirror-registry install --quayHostname mirror.registry.com --quayRoot /home/ec2-user/openshift/registry --quayStorage /home/ec2-user/openshift/mirror-storage/'
